== Date of death ==
There are different death dates reported in the literature, mainly 13 <s>February</s> March, 24 <s>February</s> March (Grove et al) and 26 <s>February</s> March (Slonimsky et al).   I trust Slonimsky over Grove, and I trust either of them over non-lexicographical sources.  

I suspect the 13 <s>February</s> March date came from someone inappropriately converting the 26 <s>February</s> March date back to the Julian calendar, despite the fact that Russia had adopted the Gregorian calendar the month before Cui died.  Immediately after then, communications being what they were, I’m sure there was a transitional period when there was a lot of confusion going on.  --  [[User:JackofOz|JackofOz]] ([[User talk:JackofOz|talk]]) 05:47, 17 July 2008 (UTC)

:According to Nazarov's biography (p. 221), the death date was March 13, at 9:30 a.m. (noting also that various encyclopedias incorrectly give the date as Mar 26). I have edited the date in the main article to reflect this. [[User:Mllefifi|Mademoiselle Fifi]] ([[User talk:Mllefifi|talk]]) 01:07, 18 July 2008 (UTC)

::Thanks for the clarification.  (I typed February above when I meant March - now corrected).  --  [[User:JackofOz|JackofOz]] ([[User talk:JackofOz|talk]]) 01:59, 18 July 2008 (UTC)

== Composer project review ==
I've reviewed this article as part of the [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Composers|Composers project]] review of its B-class articles.  This article is a decent B-class, but it has a number of issues, including aspects of his life and music that need to be elaborated.  My full review is on the [[/Comments|comments]] page; questions and comments should be left here or on my talk page. ''[[User:Magicpiano|<span style="background-color:khaki;color:firebrick;">Magic</span>]]''[[User_talk:Magicpiano|♪piano]] 01:52, 17 February 2009 (UTC)

