{{nw=}}{{nw=}}{{nw=}}Summary{{nw=}}{{nw=}}{{nw=}}
This is a pretty nice bio, but not without some issues.  One thing that troubled me was an implication that, as part of his professional and musical duties, he must have traveled fairly extensively.  However, there is not much mention of this.  (For example: he wrote about Wagner's 1876 Ring -- was he there?  Also: did he travel to see his operas performed in foreign cities?)  While he is clearly more known in the West for his music and related work, I do not think short shrift should be given to his military career -- it clearly seems important and worthy of more space than it has.

The musicology could be improved.  Most of what is described is the types of work he wrote; there is relatively little stylistic analysis, and no (or little) contemporary public or critical reaction to his works.

Article is B-class, but it could use some work. ''[[User:Magicpiano|<span style{{nw=}}"background-color:khaki;color:firebrick;">Magic</span>]]''[[User_talk:Magicpiano|♪piano]] 01:48, 17 February 2009 (UTC)}}
